# Cloudflare Pages headers (https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/headers/)
# Vite copies this file from public/ into dist/ verbatim on build.
#
# CSP is scoped to what this app actually does (verified against src/ + the
# built dist/index.html, which has no inline scripts):
#   script-src 'self'   — only same-origin bundled JS, no inline <script>.
#   style-src 'unsafe-inline' — React `style={{...}}` props are used
#     throughout (Dashboard/CaseCard/CaseDetail/BatchesSection); tightening
#     this would need a nonce pipeline this static-file approach doesn't have.
#   img-src img.youtube.com — SetCard/CaseCard link to YouTube thumbnails.
#   connect-src *.supabase.co — supabase-js (REST) + the aligner-portal-auth
#     Edge Function both live on the project's *.supabase.co origin.
# This is a best-effort static policy, not exercised against a live Cloudflare
# Access login — smoke-test the app after deploying if headers change.
/*
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self'; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: https://img.youtube.com; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://*.supabase.co; object-src 'none'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; upgrade-insecure-requests
